data.title: Kato Miliyah to cover Sheena Ringo, Utada Hikaru and more for cover album
data.meta_description: The tracklist for Kato Miliyah's first cover album "COVERS -WOMAN & MAN-" (November 25 release) has been revealed.During the coronavi…
data.text:
The tracklist for Kato Miliyah's first cover album "COVERS -WOMAN & MAN-" (November 25 release) has been revealed.

During the coronavirus state of emergency, Kato uploaded a cover video daily on her Instagram account. She decided to release the cover album as there was a huge demand from her fans. The two-disc set will include covers of Sheena Ringo's "Honnou," Utada Hikaru's "Can You Keep A Secret?, " Amuro Namie's "Don't wanna cry," Koda Kumi's "TAKE BACK," Aoyama Thelma's "Soba ni Iru ne," RADWIMPS' "me me she," Ozaki Yutaka's "OH MY LITTLE GIRL," and more.

The album will be released in both limited and regular editions. The limited-edition will come with a DVD containing an acoustic live filmed at JZ Brat Sound of Tokyo, which was the first venue she performed at.

You can check out the full tracklist as well as the jacket covers below.
